  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Andean Regional meteorological and EWS cooperation</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Secretariat of the Andean Community, national hydrometeorological services, and Finnish experts along with the Embassy of Finland in Lima have prepared a draft project document for development of the regional Early Warning System (EWS) cooperation in the Andean countries (Bolivia, Columbia, Ecuador, Peru. The aim of the cooperation is to contribute to the development and improvement of living conditions in the region by decreasing the risk of natural catastrophies and thus diminshing the socio-economic losses caused by adverse weather condition, especially floods. In order to reach the goals the capacity building of the national hydrometeorological institutes is needed. The estimated project budget is 2 million euros to be implemented during 2011-2012.</narrative>
  </description>
